==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Forced
<hw>Forced</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Done or produced with
force or great labor, or by extraordinary exertion; hurried; strained;
produced by unnatural effort or pressure; <as>as, a <ex>forced</ex>
style; a <ex>forced</ex> laugh.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Forced draught</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Draught</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Forced march</b></col>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a march of one or more days made with all
possible speed.</cd></cs></p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>For"ced*ly</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>For"ced*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

